description.narrative: Frontline health and community workers have improved capacity to provide flexible, integrated services for management of common childhood illnesses to young children in targeted emergency and non-emergency settings, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: New Element

title.narrative: Frontline health and community workers have improved capacity to provide flexible, integrated services for management of commonchildhood illnesses to young children in targeted emergency and non-emergency settings

description.narrative: Despite various implementation challenges, 821,927 children below the age of five years from Jonglei and Upper Nile were reached with lifesaving healthy services in 2021, with 99.9% coverage. This result was more than the 818,000 annual target. ;About 45% of the children were reached through the roll out of the Boma Health Initiative. Malaria (30%), Pneumonia (21%), and Diarrhea (20%) remain the top morbidity causes. Attainment of these results was possible under the leadership of the MoH in South Sudan and the financial and technical support of the World Bank, the Light Foundation, UNICEF’s strategic partners, and implementing partners.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
